Zsh

zsh is a shell designed for interactive use, although it is also a powerful scripting language.

  • Zsh SourceForge

  • Doc Ubuntu

Installation

MacOS
$ brew install zsh
$ chsh -s /usr/local/bin/zsh
Ubuntu
$ apt-get install zsh
$ chsh -s `which zsh`

Configuration

Default file for configuration
$ ~/.zshrc #

Basic Usage

$ ls **/*.txt       # extended globbing
$ ls *.[^oh]        # exclude
$ ls run<200-300>   # range
$ ls *.c~bar.c     # exclude file

cd completion

$ cd
chapters/  docs/      images/
$ cd /u/l/b/ <TAB>
$ cd /usr/local/bin/

Path replacement

$ cd /usr/local/bin
$ cd bin share
/usr/local/share

Suffix aliases

zshrc
alias -s md="code"
./README.md

And…​.

Programmable completion

zsh-completions

brew
$ brew install zsh-completions
zshrc
autoload -U compinit
compinit
$ ls -
-1  -- single column output
-A  -- list all except . and ..
-B  -- print octal escapes for control characters
-C  -- list entries in columns sorted vertically
....
ln -s 2.4.11 latest
-F      -- remove existing destination directories
-f      -- remove existing destination files
....
